---
title: "Session 6 Live Code"
author: "Carolyn Koehn"
format: html
---


This code and a few more examples can also be found on the session 6 slides.

### Access vector data:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
vector.data <- sf::st_read("/opt/data/data/assignment01/cejst_nw.shp")
```
:::




### Check the CRS:

- input
- proj4string
- wkt


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
sf::st_crs(vector.data)$input
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] "WGS 84"
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code}
sf::st_crs(vector.data)$proj4string
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] "+proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +no_defs"
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code}
sf::st_crs(vector.data)$wkt
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] "GEOGCRS[\"WGS 84\",\n    DATUM[\"World Geodetic System 1984\",\n        ELLIPSOID[\"WGS 84\",6378137,298.257223563,\n            LENGTHUNIT[\"metre\",1]]],\n    PRIMEM[\"Greenwich\",0,\n        ANGLEUNIT[\"degree\",0.0174532925199433]],\n    CS[ellipsoidal,2],\n        AXIS[\"latitude\",north,\n            ORDER[1],\n            ANGLEUNIT[\"degree\",0.0174532925199433]],\n        AXIS[\"longitude\",east,\n            ORDER[2],\n            ANGLEUNIT[\"degree\",0.0174532925199433]],\n    ID[\"EPSG\",4326]]"
```


:::
:::


### Read in raster data:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
raster.data <- terra::rast("/opt/data/data/assignment01/wildfire_hazard_agg.tif")
```
:::




### Check raster CRS:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
terra::crs(raster.data, describe=TRUE, proj=TRUE)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
     name authority code area         extent
1 unnamed      <NA> <NA> <NA> NA, NA, NA, NA
                                                                                                 proj
1 +proj=aea +lat_0=23 +lon_0=-96 +lat_1=29.5 +lat_2=45.5 +x_0=0 +y_0=0 +datum=NAD83 +units=m +no_defs
```


:::
:::


### Guess the CRS:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(sf)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
Linking to GEOS 3.11.2, GDAL 3.8.2, PROJ 9.3.1; sf_use_s2() is TRUE
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code}
#library(mapview)
locations <- data.frame(
  X = c(1200822.97857801, 1205015.51644983, 1202297.44383987, 1205877.68696743, 
        1194763.21511923, 1195463.42403192, 1199836.01037452, 1207081.96500368, 
        1201924.15986897),
  Y = c(1246476.31475063, 1248612.72571423, 1241479.45996392, 1243898.58428024, 
        1246033.7550009, 1241827.7730307, 1234691.50899912, 1251125.67808482, 
        1252188.4333016),
  id = 1:9
)

locations_sf <- st_as_sf(locations, coords = c("X", "Y"))
```
:::


We stopped this example short because of confusion with the `mapview` library. Feel free to try the code from the slides on your own time!

### Plot vector data:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
plot(st_geometry(vector.data))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](session-06-example_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-8-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### Re-project a vector:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
vector.data.proj <- vector.data %>%
  st_transform(., crs = 3083)

st_crs(vector.data.proj)$input
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] "EPSG:3083"
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code}
plot(st_geometry(vector.data.proj))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](session-06-example_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-9-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### Plot a raster:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(terra)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}

```
terra 1.7.78
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code}
plot(raster.data)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](session-06-example_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-10-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::



### Changing the CRS of a raster:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
raster.data.proj <- project(raster.data, "epsg:3083")

crs(raster.data.proj, describe=TRUE)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
                                     name authority code
1 NAD83 / Texas Centric Albers Equal Area      EPSG 3083
                         area                        extent
1 United States (USA) - Texas -106.66, -93.50, 25.83, 36.50
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code}
plot(raster.data.proj)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](session-06-example_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-11-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### Project based on another dataset:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
vector.data.proj.raster <- vector.data %>%
  st_transform(., crs = crs(raster.data))

st_crs(vector.data.proj.raster)$input
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] "PROJCRS[\"unnamed\",\n    BASEGEOGCRS[\"NAD83\",\n        DATUM[\"North American Datum 1983\",\n            ELLIPSOID[\"GRS 1980\",6378137,298.257222101004,\n                LENGTHUNIT[\"metre\",1]]],\n        PRIMEM[\"Greenwich\",0,\n            ANGLEUNIT[\"degree\",0.0174532925199433]],\n        ID[\"EPSG\",4269]],\n    CONVERSION[\"Albers Equal Area\",\n        METHOD[\"Albers Equal Area\",\n            ID[\"EPSG\",9822]],\n        PARAMETER[\"Latitude of false origin\",23,\n            ANGLEUNIT[\"degree\",0.0174532925199433],\n            ID[\"EPSG\",8821]],\n        PARAMETER[\"Longitude of false origin\",-96,\n            ANGLEUNIT[\"degree\",0.0174532925199433],\n            ID[\"EPSG\",8822]],\n        PARAMETER[\"Latitude of 1st standard parallel\",29.5,\n            ANGLEUNIT[\"degree\",0.0174532925199433],\n            ID[\"EPSG\",8823]],\n        PARAMETER[\"Latitude of 2nd standard parallel\",45.5,\n            ANGLEUNIT[\"degree\",0.0174532925199433],\n            ID[\"EPSG\",8824]],\n        PARAMETER[\"Easting at false origin\",0,\n            LENGTHUNIT[\"metre\",1],\n            ID[\"EPSG\",8826]],\n        PARAMETER[\"Northing at false origin\",0,\n            LENGTHUNIT[\"metre\",1],\n            ID[\"EPSG\",8827]]],\n    CS[Cartesian,2],\n        AXIS[\"easting\",east,\n            ORDER[1],\n            LENGTHUNIT[\"metre\",1,\n                ID[\"EPSG\",9001]]],\n        AXIS[\"northing\",north,\n            ORDER[2],\n            LENGTHUNIT[\"metre\",1,\n                ID[\"EPSG\",9001]]]]"
```


:::
:::


### Manually create polygon:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
outer = matrix(c(0,0,10,0,10,10,0,10,0,0),ncol=2, byrow=TRUE)
hole1 = matrix(c(1,1,1,2,2,2,2,1,1,1),ncol=2, byrow=TRUE)
hole2 = matrix(c(5,5,5,6,6,6,6,5,5,5),ncol=2, byrow=TRUE)
coords = list(outer, hole1, hole2)
pl1 = st_polygon(coords)
```
:::
